en_7852134_1	Six survivors walked to a remote village where they said that 44 people, mostly from Ghana and Nigeria and including three babies and two other children, died of thirst.
en_7852134_2	The number of migrants who cross the Sahara has increased in recent years as impoverished West Africans risk their lives to try to reach Europe.
en_7852134_3	In one of the most perilous parts of the journey, thousands of migrants each week are crammed into pick-up trucks for the days-long ride from Niger into Libya, often with only enough room for a few liters of water.
en_7852134_4	Authorities and aid organizations are able to keep track of the thousands of migrant deaths in the Mediterranean Sea between Africa and Europe, but is it almost impossible to know how many have died in the vast Sahara.
